## Description
The **Publish Documents (Pweb) **task creates Pwebs, loads them on Digital Archiving, and returns the pURL.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Store **field and select the Pweb Store resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [Pweb Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/pweb-store-resource-reference).

- Click on the **Resource **field and select the Pweb Template resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [Pweb Template Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/pweb-template-resource-reference).

- Toggle the **Generate Purl **option to generate a Purl for the published Pweb. Untoggle this option to publish Pvideo without generating a Purl.

> Note

This option is enabled by default.

> Note

It is possible to generate a Purl for a previously published Pweb through API. For more information, see [Purl Generator API](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Doxee%2BPlatform%2B3%2BPurl%2BGenerator%2BAPI).

In the **Format **field, select one of the options:

**Signed**: Produce a Purl with alert features in cases of unauthorized alterations.

- **Plain**: Produce an unsigned Purl.

> Important

Workflows created before the **Doxee Platform 3.44 release **will by default produce plain (unsigned) Purls to ensure retro-compatibility.

However, the produced Purls will nevertheless be significantly longer than Purls produced before the release. To shorten the links, see [Shorten Links Batch Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/shorten-links-batch-workflow-task-reference).

- *(optional) *In the **TTL **field, enter a retention period for the Purl.

## 
## Input
The input of the task is an XML file with a specific structure.

> Note

For more information on the structure of the input file, see [XML Input File Structure for Doxee Platform 3 Native Tasks#Pweb production](/doxee-platform/docs/xml-input-file-structure-for-doxee-platform-3-native-tasks-2#pweb-production).

## Output
The output of the task is the input XML file enriched with the Pweb metadata.

### Output branches
The **Publish Documents (Pweb) **task's output may be connected by the following branch types:

**Branch type**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Default**

X

Indicates how the Pweb will be delivered (for example: via SMS and email)

**Discard**

Indicates the action to perform on any discarded outputs (for example: save on an FTP folder)
